A vintage 1960s-style illustration of an elaborate mechanical contraption resembling a Rube Goldberg machine, featuring brass gears, copper pipes, and analog dials. On one side, ornate scrollwork name tags with decorative calligraphy flow into the machine through a funnel. The contraption processes them through spinning drums, rotating conveyor belts, and clicking mechanical switches. On the output side, clean streamlined envelopes with @ symbols embossed emerge onto a polished wooden tray. The color palette uses warm sepia tones, aged cream paper textures, and touches of tarnished gold. Small steam wisps rise from various joints of the machine, suggesting active transformation. The background shows a craftsman's workshop with wooden shelves holding mysterious bottles and tools, bathed in warm amber lamplight filtering through dusty windows.
